The paper deals with the Fourier Entropy-Influence Conjecture, which is a problem in computational complexity theory and Boolean function analysis. The paper uses techniques from coding theory and information theory, which suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with extremal cases of Boolean functions, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses read-k decision trees and DNFs, which suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) may also be a relevant sub-category.
